1. Interrupt hota kya hai?

Interrupt ka matlab hota hai thread ko signal dena ki:

“Bhai, ab apna kaam check kar, shayad rukna ya exit karna pade.”

⚠️ Important:
Interrupt thread ko zabardasti band nahi karta — thread khud decide karta hai ki kya karna hai.

2. Interrupt kaise bhejte hain?

Jis thread ko interrupt karna hai, uspe interrupt() call kar do:

thread.interrupt();

3. Thread kaise react karega?
Case 1: Agar thread sleep() ya wait() jaise blocking method use kar raha hai

Tab interrupt hone par InterruptedException throw hota hai:

try {
    Thread.sleep(4000);
} catch (InterruptedException e) {
    // Thread ko signal mila ki ruk ja
    return; // thread exit
}

Case 2: Agar thread kaam me busy hai (long loop ya processing)

Tab thread ko khud check karna padega:

for (int i = 0; i < 1000; i++) {
    System.out.println("Working..." + i);

    if (Thread.interrupted()) {
        System.out.println("Interrupt signal mila, thread exit ho raha hai...");
        return;
    }
}

4. Interrupt flag ka funda

Jab hum interrupt() call karte hain:

Ek flag set ho jata hai ki “thread ko signal mila hai.”

Thread.interrupted() → flag check karega aur clear bhi kar dega.

isInterrupted() → flag check karega but clear nahi karega.

5. Yaad rakhne layak baatein

Interrupt ka matlab force stop nahi hai, bas ek polite request hai.

Agar thread ne signal ko check nahi kiya, toh wo chalta rahega.

Best practice: hamesha loop ya blocking points par interrupt ko handle karo.

Easy Example
class MyThread extends Thread {
    public void run() {
        for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
            System.out.println("Working..." + i);

            if (Thread.interrupted()) {
                System.out.println("Interrupt mila, thread band ho raha hai...");
                return;
            }
        }
    }
}

public class InterruptDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws InterruptedException {
        MyThread t1 = new MyThread();
        t1.start();

        Thread.sleep(20); // thoda wait
        t1.interrupt();   // signal bhej do
    }
}


Output:

Working...0
Working...1
Interrupt mila, thread band ho raha hai...

